      "thumbnailUrl": "https://i.ytimg.com/vi/mv5MFPKLNYw/hqdefault.jpg",
      "name": "How to Print from the Lower Paper Tray on Canon PIXMA G6020 - Easy Printing Guide",
      "description": "📺 Learn how to easily print from the lower paper tray on your Canon PIXMA G6020! Watch this video to find out how.\n\n📖 In 6 steps:\n1. Open the rear tray cover and extend the paper support.\n2. Open the feed slot cover and slide the right-hand side paper guide to the far right.\n3. Load paper with the print side facing up and adjust the side paper guide.\n4. Close the feed slot cover.\n5. Select the paper size and type on the printer’s screen, then press OK.\n6. Ensure the paper output tray is pulled out and follow any additional on-screen instructions.\n\n🔔 Subscribe:\nSubscribe to our channel and stay informed about the latest questions and answers!\nhttps://www.youtube.com/channel/UCuudCQgaIlFo9CenuC9cudQ \n\n📚💬 Manual and other questions:\nOn our site, you can find the complete manual for the Canon PIXMA G6020. There, you can also ask your question to other Canon PIXMA G6020 users.\n🔗https://www.manua.ls/canon/pixma-g6020/manual\n\nMusic by Shane Ivers – https://www.silvermansound.com\n\n#CANON #PIXMAG6020 #PRINTER #PRINT",
      "uploadDate": "2024-06-04T15:09:03.000Z",
      "embedUrl": "https://www.youtube.com/embed/mv5MFPKLNYw"
    },
    {
      "@type": "DiscussionForumPosting",
