</div></button></div></div></div><div class="ad-placeholder my-3" style="" data-v-54cc08af data-v-65ff48d5><!----><!----></div><!--]--><!--[--><div class="faq-item" itemscope itemprop="mainEntity" itemtype="https://schema.org/Question" data-v-54cc08af data-v-d2242a65><h4 class="h5" itemprop="text name" data-v-d2242a65><!--[-->My prints are coming out blurry, how can I improve print quality on my Canon PIXMA G6020?<!--]--></h4><div itemscope itemprop="acceptedAnswer" itemtype="https://schema.org/Answer" data-v-d2242a65><div itemprop="text" data-v-d2242a65><!--[-->Firstly, make sure you are using high-quality paper suitable for your printing needs. Clean the print head nozzles using the printer&#39;s utility software to remove any clogs. Adjust the print quality settings in the printer preferences to a higher resolution if necessary.<!--]--></div><div class="faq-item__footer" data-v-d2242a65><button class="outline-primary like sm" data-v-d2242a65><div class="app-icon size-null thumbs-up" data-v-d2242a65><svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 16 16" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"><path d="M8.759 1.104 C 8.344 1.205,7.888 1.528,7.668 1.878 C 7.533 2.093,7.470 2.268,7.373 2.701 C 7.237 3.308,7.137 3.564,6.885 3.950 C 6.714 4.212,6.483 4.456,6.105 4.775 C 5.773 5.055,5.605 5.229,5.426 5.480 C 5.310 5.642,5.067 6.100,5.067 6.156 C 5.067 6.228,5.022 6.175,4.949 6.020 C 4.791 5.679,4.385 5.362,4.005 5.283 C 3.814 5.243,1.946 5.243,1.755 5.283 C 1.306 5.376,0.911 5.729,0.743 6.187 L 0.680 6.360 0.680 9.573 L 0.680 12.787 0.740 12.945 C 0.904 13.376,1.273 13.716,1.694 13.826 C 1.925 13.886,3.835 13.886,4.066 13.826 C 4.488 13.716,4.861 13.371,5.020 12.943 C 5.073 12.801,5.080 12.721,5.093 12.067 L 5.107 11.347 5.194 11.514 C 5.392 11.893,5.666 12.243,5.934 12.462 C 6.195 12.674,7.344 13.434,7.594 13.560 C 7.859 13.693,8.192 13.796,8.492 13.838 C 8.618 13.856,9.272 13.866,10.195 13.866 C 11.857 13.866,11.906 13.862,12.248 13.696 C 12.481 13.584,12.748 13.367,1